Black Friday has become the biggest shopping day on the calendar, with a growing list of South African retailers offering greatly reduced prices on a range of products. While Black Friday is set to fall on 28 November 2020, a number of retailers have announced extended deal dates due to the coronavirus pandemic and possible overcrowding. Online retailers are also expected to offer a number of specials on ‘Cyber Monday’, which falls on 30 November in 2019. Below is a list of stores which have confirmed that they will be offering Black Friday deals on and around the day. Bidorbuy.co.za <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-450643" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Bidorbuy-logo.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Bidorbuy-logo.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Bidorbuy-logo-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Builders <img class="size-full wp-image-210639 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Builders.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Builders.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Builders-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Cell C <img class="size-full wp-image-302352 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cell-C-pin-drop.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cell-C-pin-drop.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cell-C-pin-drop-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Cell